{
  "text": "Since V \u2022 is aCech resolution of X, we have Q tr (V \u2022 ) \u223c = Q tr (X) by [MVW, Proposition 6.12] . This proves the result. Proof. We can assume that F is connected. By 3.3 we get a sequence of blow-ups with smooth centers \u03c0 : F \u2032 \u2192 F such that F \u2032 has (quasi)-projective coarse moduli space. By 3.6 M (F ) is a direct summand of M (F \u2032 ). By [CITATION_1] Theorem 1] there exists a smooth (quasi)-projective variety X and a finite flat morphism g : X \u2192 F \u2032 . Hence M (F \u2032 ) is a direct summand of M (X) which proves our claim. ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "119615177"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "119615177": {
      "title": "On coverings of Deligne-Mumford Stacks and surjectivity of the Brauer map",
      "abstract": "This paper proves a result on the existence of finite flat scheme covers of Deligne-Mumford stacks. This result is used to prove that a large class of smooth Deligne-Mumford stacks with affine moduli space are quotient stacks, and in the case of quasi-projective moduli space, to reduce the question to one concerning Brauer groups of schemes."
    }
  }
}